                        "hint": "Formula for calculating percentages <br>\nThe formula for calculating percentages or for converting from percentages are relatively simple.  <br>\nTo convert a fraction or decimal to a percentage, multiply by 100:\n\n<figure class=\"figure\" style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 15px 0 5px;\"><img name=\"0002h\" src=https://examineer.org/potato/graphics/0002h/c8718749-6af2-4a62-9c63-3bf8327667a0 alt=\"image not found\" style=\"width:70%;min-width:100px;background-color:#FAFAFA;padding:7px;border-radius:7px;\"><figcaption style=\"font-family:Arial;font-size:70%;\">Calculating percentage</figcaption></figure>\n\nTo convert a percentage to a fraction, divide by 100 and reduce the fraction (if possible):\n\n<figure class=\"figure\" style=\"text-align:center;margin:0 15px 0 5px;\"><img name=\"0002i\" src=https://examineer.org/potato/graphics/0002i/6e65cbf4-0010-44a0-9462-ed3eb95e003c alt=\"image not found\" style=\"width:70%;min-width:100px;background-color:#FAFAFA;padding:7px;border-radius:7px;\"><figcaption style=\"font-family:Arial;font-size:70%;\">Calculating percentage</figcaption></figure>",
                        "explanation": "Average sales (in thousand number) of branches B1, B3 and B6 in 2000  <br>\n\n<math><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8290;</mo><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mrow><mo>&#215;</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>95</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>70</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mfrac><mn>245</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></math>\n  .....<b>(a) </b>        <br>\nAverage sales (in thousand number) of branches B1, B2 and B3 in 2001    <br>\n \n<math><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8290;</mo><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mrow><mo>&#215;</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>105</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>65</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>110</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mfrac><mn>280</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></math>\n    .....<b>(b) </b>  <br>\n \n<math><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>\n   Required percentage =  \n\n<math><mrow><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac><mo>&#8290;</mo><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mrow><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></mrow><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8202;</mtext><mrow><mtext>87.5</mtext><mtext>%</mtext></mrow></mrow></math>\n         \n\n"
